# EAS uploads from the repo root (this is where .git lives), so without this it
# packages the WHOLE monorepo — web/ alone is ~829MB — and the upload dies with
# ECONNRESET on anything but a perfect connection. Only mobile/ is needed to build
# the app; EAS installs its dependencies itself from package.json + lockfile.

# Secrets — must never leave the machine
**/play-service-account.json
**/*firebase-adminsdk*.json
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Other workspaces — irrelevant to the mobile build
web/
backend/

# Dependencies and build output anywhere in the tree
**/node_modules/
**/.expo/
**/dist/
**/web-build/
**/.next/
**/build/

# Native folders are regenerated by prebuild during the build
mobile/android/
mobile/ios/

# Editor / OS / tooling noise
.git/
.claude/
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/README.md
**/CLAUDE.md
**/AGENTS.md
